BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Film: MOULIN ROUGE!
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260430T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260430T210000
UID:ai1ec-148915-95207@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Set against the Parisian backdrop of a spectacular Moulin Roug
 e show\, an idealistic young writer (Ewan McGregor) is drafted into a bohe
 mian entourage and falls in love with an ambitious\, stunning\, and ultima
 tely doomed courtesan (Nicole Kidman)\, who is caught between the hero she
 ’s falling for\, too\, and a ruthless duke\, whose fortune could help sa
 ve her and the Moulin Rouge. McGregor and Kidman lead an internationally r
 enowned cast in this swooningly romantic and pop-music-inspired dancing an
 d singing extravaganza with musical inspiration from the likes of David Bo
 wie\, Beck\, Labelle\, Madonna\, and Fatboy Slim. The film would go on to 
 inspire the Broadway stage production ofMoulin Rouge! The Musical. [127 mi
 n\; musical\, drama\, romance\; English\, French\, and Spanish with Englis
 h subtitles]
LOCATION:IU Cinema\, 1213 E. 7th Street\, Bloomington (on the North end of
  the IU Auditorium)
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/film-moulin-rouge/?instance_id=95207
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
