BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sycamore Land Trust Spring Plant Sale\, to benefit their Native Pl
 ant Nursery
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260502T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260502T140000
UID:ai1ec-148548-94975@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Our fifth annual Spring Plant Sale on Saturday\, May 2\, will 
 offer over 45 species of native plants that were homegrown in our Native P
 lant Nursery from seed to plant plug. Many species are grown from locally 
 collected seed at nearby preserves. All species are ethically sourced and 
 native to southern Indiana\, providing benefits to local pollinators and w
 ildlife.All proceeds going back into nursery operations and native plant r
 estoration projects. Stop by to learn from experienced staff and volunteer
 s on the advantages of gardening with native species!Learn more about our 
 sale and view descriptions\, cultural requirements\, and benefits to wildl
 ife for each available species at sycamorelandtrust.org/plant-sale 🌼
LOCATION:Bloomingfoods East Parking Lot\, 3220 E 3rd Street\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/sycamore-land-trust-spring-plant-sale-to-benefi
 t-their-native-plant-nursery/?instance_id=94975
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
