BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Saturday Crafternoon
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260502T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260502T140000
UID:ai1ec-148767-95109@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Saturday Crafternoons in May celebrate the Wylie House Museum
 ’s newest exhibition\, Louisa’s Garden\, opening May 1st. The exhibiti
 on highlights Louisa Wylie Boisen\, eldest daughter of IU professor Theoph
 ilus Wylie\, and her accomplishments as a brave\, complex\, and cherished 
 woman. Her horticultural impact can still be seen at the Wylie House today
 \, over 70 years later! You’re invited to come to the Wylie House Museum
  every Saturday in May and make your own mini Wylie House Museum garden to
  cherish\, in memory of Louise Boisen Wylie.
LOCATION:Wylie House Museum\, 307 E 2nd St\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/saturday-crafternoon-at-the-wylie-house-9/?inst
 ance_id=95109
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Finn: A New Musical- At the PB&J Cafe
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260502T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260502T140000
UID:ai1ec-140265-90568@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage & Screen presents “Finn: A New Musical- 
 At the PB&J Cafe\,” on stage May 1-17 at the Waldron Auditorium.From the
  creator of Doc McStuffins and Vampirina\, Finn is a heartwarming musical 
 adventure about a young shark on the brink of growing up. As he prepares t
 o join the fearsome Shark Guard\, Finn can’t shake the feeling that he
 ’s different from the other sharks. Deep inside\, he discovers a colorfu
 l fish inside him—a part of himself that longs to sparkle\, sing\, and d
 ance. As Finn embarks on a journey of self-discovery\, friendship\, and ad
 venture\, he finds the courage to be himself! Fun for all ages!PB&J Cafe: 
 A Dinner Theater for Kids! At the PB&J Cafe\, young theatergoers will enjo
 y a meal during the performance and leave with autographs from their favor
 ite characters.
LOCATION:Waldron Arts Center (122 S Walnut St)
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/finn-a-new-musical-at-the-pbj-cafe-2/?instance_
 id=90568
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
