BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Godzilla Weekend: Mothra Madness – FILM FESTIVAL
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260613T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260613T181500
UID:ai1ec-148359-94923@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:It’s officially MOTHRA DAY in Bloomington on June 12th!The p
 roclamation (see below) has been signed.BCT’s 2nd annual Godzilla Weeken
 dis showcasing this giant moth that attacks the whole world with fury!DAY 
 TWO will feature three essential Godzilla films along. Presented byThe Eas
 t Asian Studies Center\,The Media School\,Tattoo Kaiju\, and Buskirk-Chuml
 ey Theater.Talks\, vendors\, and additional Godzilla fun and performances 
 in between!Doors open at 11AM !Mothra vs. Godzilla(Ishiro Honda\, 1964) 12
 PM – 1:30PMGodzilla faces off against the benevolent insect monster-god 
 Mothra in this clash of the titans\, a crossover battle between two of Toh
 o Studios’ most popular monsters—the last in which Godzilla would figu
 re as a malevolent villain rather than a fearsome hero. Mothra vs. Godzill
 a marks a creative high point in the Godzilla series\, with pointed social
  commentary from director Ishiro Honda\, a masterful score by Akira Ifukub
 e\, and astonishing special-effects work by Eiji Tsuburaya.DCP FormatSubti
 tledNot Rated1hr 29minsDestroy All Monsters(Ishiro Honda\, 1968) 2:15PM 
 – 3:45PMThe original Godzilla team of director Ishiro Honda\, special-ef
 fects supervisor Eiji Tsuburaya\, and composer Akira Ifukube reunited for 
 this kaiju extravaganza\, which features no fewer than eleven monsters. Se
 t in the remote future of 1999\, when the people of Earth have achieved wo
 rld peace by confining destructive creatures to Monsterland (until an alie
 n race intervenes)\, Destroy All Monsters mounts a thrilling display of in
 novative action sequences and memorable images that have made it a favorit
 e for generations of viewers.DCP FormatSubtitledNot Rated1hr 29minsGodzill
 a\, Mothra\, and King Ghidorah: Giant Monsters All Out Attack(Shusuke Kane
 ko 2001)4:30PM – 6:15PMIn this brand-new adventure\, Godzilla returns to
  his “bad guy” roots as he rampages through Japan just like in the goo
 d ol’ days. In response\, an ancient religious sect resurrects the legen
 dary “Holy Beasts of Yamato” (Ghidorah\, Mothra and Baragon) to protec
 t Japan and destroy the threat of Godzilla forever.DCP FormatSubtitledNot 
 Rated1hr 45mins
LOCATION:Buskirk-Chumley Theater: 114 E. Kirkwood Ave
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/godzilla-weekend-mothra-madness-film-festival/?
 instance_id=94923
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
